                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d499">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Fox</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Ecuadorian Congress met yesterday extraordinary session. President’s message<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d499fn1">See <ref target="#pg_463">p. 463</ref>
                    </note> discusses situation historically, saying Ecuador has accepted mediation
                    warmly; congratulates mediating powers; says that Chile could not take part on
                    account interrupted relations with Peru; points out that Colombia on account of
                    existing treaties must be included in settlement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
